1 Montana veteran population. The Montana veterans' affairs division may form an advisory committee comprised
2 of stakeholders to assist with the survey.
3 (4) (5) The study must evaluate existing veterans' home services and the configuration of those
4 services with respect to the needs identified.
5 (5) (6) The study must include an analysis of the need for additional state veterans' cemeteries,
6 including their placement within the state.
7 (7) The Montana veterans' affairs division shall prepare an outreach and marketing plan prior to
8 the start of the study."
9
10 Section 2. Section 10-2-902, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "10-2-902. Department of public health and human services Montana veterans' affairs division
12 to conduct study. The staff of the senior and long-term care division within the department of public health and
13 human services Montana veterans' affairs division shall conduct the decennial veterans' long-term care needs
14 study. The staff of the Montana veterans' affairs division senior and long-term care division within the
15 department of public health and human services shall provide support as needed."
16
17 Section 3. Section 10-2-903, MCA, is amended to read:
18 "10-2-903. Survey report required Reporting requirements -- plan and budget. (1) (a) During the
19 interim prior to the availability of the most recent federal census data, the staff of the Montana veterans' affairs
20 division shall present a plan for conducting the study required in 10-2-901, including a budget estimate, to the
21 state administration and veterans' affairs interim committee.
22 (b) After hearing the study plan and budget estimate, the state administration and veterans' affairs
23 interim committee may request a committee bill with an appropriation to fund the study.
24 (2) The Montana veterans' affairs division shall provide at least one update to the state
25 administration and veterans' affairs interim committee while the study is being conducted. The committee may
26 request additional updates as needed.
27 (3) As soon as possible after the completion of the decennial survey study, the department of
28 public health and human services and the Montana veterans' affairs division, in consultation with the
